# === gitban overlay ===========================================================
# Strategy: this is a FORK of XTraceAI/memory-sdk-ts used as our gitban
# workspace. We TRACK the durable PM/dispatch surface (.gitban cards, roadmap,
# hooks, agent inboxes + .claude agents/skills/settings) so that parallel
# subagent worktrees — which are checkouts of HEAD and therefore only receive
# *tracked* files — come up with the harness intact. A blanket `.gitban/**`
# ignore would leave every worktree missing its hooks/cards and thrash dispatch.
# Only the regenerable, machine-local runtime artifacts below are ignored.
# (See .claude/CLAUDE.md → "Contributing & gitban overlay" for the full why.)
.claude/worktrees/
.gitban/agents/.active-log
.gitban/agents/*/logs/*.jsonl
.gitban/agents/*/logs/*.jsonl.*
.gitban/agents/traces/
.gitban/audit/
.gitban/.viewer-port
.gitban/views/
.gitignore.gitban
/log/
